    "attributes": {
        "action": "Allow indoor theatre and live events in Tier 3 areas if they are covid-secure!",
        "additional_details": "Non-essential retail has been allowed to open as the Christmas trade is deemed essential for their business. Pantomime is no different for the theatre industry; many theatres only survive on their pantomime season. Theatres and indoor venues have spent months of effort and money making their spaces covid-secure, and cannot open, despite being potentially safer than a shopping trip, hairdresser visit or gym workout.",
        "background": "If theatres and indoor venues are covid-secure: socially distanced seating, temperature checks, face masks, hand sanitiser, ventilation, enhanced cleaning and use of track and trace, please let them open.",
